icipality]] in the west, [[Godawari, Sudurpashchim|Godawari Municipality]] in the east, [[Mohanyal]] and [[Chure Rural Municipality]] in the north and [[Dhangadhi|Dhangadhi Sub Metropolitan City]] and [[Kailari Rural Municipality]] in the south.\n\n==Census==\nTotal population of Gauriganga Municipality is 58,286,. Chhetree is the dominant caste followed by Tharu Ethnic group. [[Brahmin]] Ranked third with. The male to female sex-ratio is 96.47. Total 5,293 household. <ref>Nepal census 2011</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.un.org.np/maps/district-maps/western/Kailali.pdf UN map of the municipalities of Kailali District]\n*[http://www.ddckailali.gov.np Official website of ddc Kaialali]\n*[https://www.citypopulation.de/php/nepal-mun-admin.php?adm2id=7105 City Population - Gauriganga Municipality in Nepal]\n{{Kailali District}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Kailali District]]\n[[Category:Municipalities in Sudurpashchim Pradesh]]\n\n{{Sudurpashchim-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "R'n'B", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:Ward\u2192Ward (electoral subdivision); Unlinked:11", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gauriganga"}
